HB 895 Original 2026 Regular Session Boyd
Abstract: Requires a healthcare provider to provide, at minimum, a three-day supply of
post-exposure prophylaxis to all survivors of sexual assault.
Present law provides that a survivor of sexual assault must be provided any medication
during the forensic medical examination, including emergency contraception and HIV or STI
prophylaxis.
Proposed law modifies present law requiring the healthcare provider to provide, at a
minimum, three days of HIV or STI post-exposure prophylaxis during the forensic medical
exam.
(Amends R.S. 40:1216.1(A)(2)(e))
